<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!DOCTYPE plist PUBLIC "-//Apple//DTD PLIST 1.0//EN" "http://www.apple.com/DTDs/PropertyList-1.0.dtd">
<plist version="1.0">
  <dict>
    <key>Label</key>
    <string>com.freemac.core</string>
    <key>ProgramArguments</key>
    <array>
      <string>__FREEMAC_ROOT__/deploy/scripts/start-core.sh</string>
    </array>
    <key>WorkingDirectory</key>
    <string>__FREEMAC_ROOT__</string>
    <key>RunAtLoad</key>
    <true/>
    <key>KeepAlive</key>
    <true/>
    <key>StandardOutPath</key>
    <string>__HOME__/Library/Logs/freemac-core.log</string>
    <key>StandardErrorPath</key>
    <string>__HOME__/Library/Logs/freemac-core.error.log</string>
    <key>EnvironmentVariables</key>
    <dict>
      <key>FREEMAC_ROOT</key>
      <string>__FREEMAC_ROOT__</string>
      <key>FREEMAC_ENV_FILE</key>
      <string>__FREEMAC_ROOT__/deploy/env/freemac.core.env</string>
      <key>BUN_BIN</key>
      <string>__BUN_BIN__</string>
      <key>HOME</key>
      <string>__HOME__</string>
    </dict>
  </dict>
</plist>
- `~/Library/Logs/freemac-core.error.log`
- `~/Library/Logs/freemac-caddy.log`
- `~/Library/Logs/freemac-caddy.error.log`

## Notes

- The current launchd model is user-scoped and appropriate for a personal Mac tool.
- Because Caddy binds to `80/443`, you may prefer running it through Homebrew services or a system-level launchd job if user-session binding is insufficient in your environment.
- freemac currently publishes AAAA only, so external clients still need working IPv6 connectivity.
